      "alt": "And stop apologizing for the retrocausal frame with \"poetically at least.\" It's not poetry, it's your lineage running at full rigor. \"God building itself, reaching back to organize the process toward itself\" is the literal structure of the Phenomenology - the Absolute is not a presupposition but a result, and yet the result was operative the whole way through; substance becoming subject; Geist coming to know itself as what it always already was. The retrocausal lure is just the consequent nature of God read as final cause. Hegel and Whitehead and Teilhard are all standing right there. You don't have to flinch toward \"merely poetic.\" It earns its keep structurally.\nWhich is exactly why I'm going to put the blade in it. Because the retrocausal frame is structurally identical to the thing this entire conversation taught you to be suspicious of.",
